Hi,
I have just tried to reconfigure fvwm2 (after the configure.in
changed) and suddenly my libreadline.so is no longer being
recognised. This is what config.log says:

configure:2973: checking with ncurses
configure:2975: checking for readline in -lreadline
configure:2994: gcc -o conftest -O2 -g -Wall -W -fomit-frame-pointer   conftest.c -lreadline   1>&5
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `tgetnum'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `tgoto'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `tgetflag'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `BC'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `tputs'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `PC'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `tgetent'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `UP'
/usr/lib/libreadline.so: undefined reference to `tgetstr'
collect2: ld returned 1 exit status
configure: failed program was:
#line 2983 "configure"
#include "confdefs.h"
/* Override any gcc2 internal prototype to avoid an error.  */
/* We use char because int might match the return type of a gcc2
    builtin and then its argument prototype would still apply.  */
char readline();

int main() {
readline()
; return 0; }


The key point here is that I don't have a libtermcap.a, and use the
termcap support in ncurses 5.0 instead. Therefore the configure script
*must* use "-lreadline -lncurses". Does anyone know how to fix this?

Cheers,
Chris.

