On Tue, Apr 04, 2000 at 12:37:06AM -0500, Eric Renfro wrote:
> In fvwm 2.0.0 and up, does fvwm's PipeRead read only STDIN? If I print to
> STDERR in a script, will the PipeRead pick that up, or will it be ignored?

PipeRead reads only from STDIN, not from stderr (if you read
from both, you can't know the order in which you have to
parse the input lines).  You probably know this, but just in
case you don't:  you can redirect all output to stderr to
stdin with '2>&1':

  grep "foo" bar 2>&1

Bye

Dominik ^_^

