Hello,

I think that there is a FVWM_USERHOME bug:
In some sense fvwm know FVWM_USERHOME even if it
is not set: in this case fvwm consider that $HOME
is $FVWM_USERHOME and some time (I do not understand
when and why) it is really set to HOME (try
the FvwmScript:
Set $F = (GetOutput {echo $FVWM_USERHOME} 1 -1)
Do {Echo } $F
with $FVWM_USERHOME not set the result is:
[FVWM][Echo]: $HOME   !!??!!?

I think that if the user do not set FVWM_USERHOME then
fvwm have to set it. Moreover, I think that the better
idea is to set it to ~/.fvwm in this case. Why ? because
imagine a user which start fvwm2 without config, then
he use the Setup Form and the Form copy 10 (non cached) 
files: DefaultFvwmBacker, Default* ... in ~/  !? 

Moreover, we can imagine a Welcome Script or Form that 
gives the choice between 

1. Setup Form
2. the future Setup95 Script
3. loading a .fvwm2rc from somewhere

and which is started if no configuration file is
found (E.g., FVWM_CONFIGDIR/system.fvwm2rc may contain
one line which start this Script/Form).

I'm ready to do a Welcome script.

Olivier

