Olivier Chapuis <olivier.chapuis@free.fr> writes:
> Hello,
> 
> Moreover, we can imagine a Welcome Script or Form that 
> gives the choice between 
> 
> 1. Setup Form
> 2. the future Setup95 Script
> 3. loading a .fvwm2rc from somewhere
> 
> and which is started if no configuration file is
> found (E.g., FVWM_CONFIGDIR/system.fvwm2rc may contain
> one line which start this Script/Form).
> 
> I'm ready to do a Welcome script.

I don't understand what you are proposing.

We already have a setup form, "modules/FvwmForm/FormFvwmSetup.in".
Is that the same thing you are referring to in "1" above?

We don't really use anything from system.fvwm2rc  anymore, all of that
has been moved into a number of installable config files starting with
fvwm/ConfigFvwmSetup which gets installed as $FVWM_USERHOME/.fvwm2rc
by the setup form.  (Is'nt that the same thing you are describing in
"3" above?)

If you want to extend this to install a "95" type setup,
FormFvwmSetup would be the logical place to do it.

If you want to rewrite FormFvwmSetup using FvwmScript, I don't see
any problem with that.

