Around line 410 in decorations.c:

#ifdef SHAPE
  if (ShapesSupported)
  {
    if(t->wShaped)
      decor &= ~(DECOR_BORDER|MWM_DECOR_RESIZEH);
  }
#endif

Disable it and you can get titles on shaped windows.
I suspect this is a change from the early days of fvwm
because I had a "Style xeyes NoTilte" line in my .fvwm2rc
that isn't necessary any more.

There must be other things  at work since  this turns off the  border,
and I end up with a title bar but still  no border.  I also killed the
code in add_window.c around line 432 but I still didn't have a border.

I'm not suggesting changing anything.  I'm just looking at the options
for a FAQ answer for the "desktop launcher" question.

