No, imagine that a user upgrade from 2.2.x to 2.4.X but now the default
installation for the config file is ~/.fvwm/.fvwm2rc. Then, with 3 he
can install the old ~/.fvwm2rc file in ~/.fvwm/ (and get some little pbs).
About the system.fvwm2rc my idea is that if a new user start fvwm without
config then fvwm gives some feedback: a welcome Script/Form is started
that give some instruction to install a config file (if not with some
new unix user it is: Ctl-Alt-F1, killall -9 fvwm2 because he see only
a grey screen). So my proposition for system.fvwm2rc is a one line config:
AddToFunc StartFunction I FvwmForm/Script Form/ScriptWelcome

> 
> If you want to extend this to install a "95" type setup,
> FormFvwmSetup would be the logical place to do it.
>

I suggest that the default config and sample-95 (and may be
other configs) have its own config script/form. For example,
for sample-95 I do a quite elaborated script that allows the
user to set some preferences (as the FormFvwmSetup ask the
user about adding modules configs). I will try to commit
as soon as possible my work on sample-95 for clarification.

Olivier

