Hi all, I'm fiddling with dynamic menus again. I play with them on and
off, but at this point, I'm fairly certain that something funny's
happening. The current version that I'm working with is at

http://www.best.com/~mikehan/PerlMenu

The output it yields looks like this:

AddToMenu /home/mikehan MissingSubmenuFunction MakeMissingMenu
AddToMenu /home/mikehan DynamicPopdownAction DestroyMenu recreate /home/mikehan
AddToMenu /home/mikehan 1 Popup /home/mikehan/1
AddToMenu /home/mikehan 107 Popup /home/mikehan/107
AddToMenu /home/mikehan 120 Popup /home/mikehan/120
AddToMenu /home/mikehan 134 Popup /home/mikehan/134
...

Note that I defined:

AddToMenu /home/mikehan DynamicPopupAction PipeRead PerlMenu /home/mikehan
AddToFunc MakeMissingMenu I PipeRead PerlMenu $0

When I try to popup a submenu of /home/mikehan, such as
/home/mikehan/1, I get a bunch of errors:

[FVWM][add_item_to_menu]: <<ERROR>> menu /home/mikehan is in use

and no submenu ever pops up.

I'm confused. Can anyone out there who knows about the dynamic menu
stuff tell me if I'm doing something that's obviously wrong? Output
from PerlMenu when invoked for a submenu looks like this:

AddToMenu /home/mikehan/1 MissingSubmenuFunction MakeMissingMenu
AddToMenu /home/mikehan/1 DynamicPopdownAction DestroyMenu recreate
/home/mikehan/1
AddToMenu /home/mikehan/1 /home/mikehan/1 Nop

If I add a "Beep" to the head of the output, when I navigate onto the
item with a submenu I get a bunch of beeps, so I know that FVWM is
correctly executing the missing submenu function. The only thing I can
think of right now is that somehow FVWM is trying to addtomenu to
/home/mikehan instead of /home/mikehan/1.

So, any thoughts?

By the way, while trying to figure this out, I discovered that the
manpage is wrong. The manpage says that the token for missing submenu
creation is "MissingSubmenuFunc" but the code really works with
"MissingSubmenuFunction". I have a manpage patch attached, though
perhaps the manpage is "right" and the code is wrong?
