That looks really nice :-)  Good old FvwmButtons always has a
surprise ready for you.

> It seems to work, but I'm not sure I'm  using documented behavior with
> the "Pixmap none" being overridden by the "(Back".

What you're doing is okay; but transparency isn't well documented.
Looking at the code I see that with transparency enabled:

 1) Reliefs and all parts not belonging to a button are transparent.
 2) Button icons are transparent where the icon itself is transparent.
 3) Button titles are *not* transparent.

(3) is a bit surprising.  From SetTransparentBackground() (FvwmButtons.c):

line 560 ff.

  /*
   * if button has an icon, draw a rect with the same size as the icon
   * (or the mask of the icon),
   * else draw a rect with the same size as the button.
   */
  if(b->flags&b_Icon)
  {
    ...
  }
  else
  {
    number=buttonNum(b);
    XFillRectangle(Dpy,pmap_mask,trans_gc,buttonXPos(b,number),
      buttonYPos(b,number),
      buttonWidth(b),buttonHeight(b));
  }

> I'm also not sure about doing the icon as 1x3  to get the label placed
> right.
>
> Any comments?

1) Try using specific geometries for buttons and the whole window:

# FvwmButtons icon launcher:
DestroyFunc Launcher
AddToFunc Launcher
+ I DestroyModuleConfig $0Launch.*
+ I *$0Launch.Geometry 64x68
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+ I *$0Launch.Columns 1
+ I *$0Launch.Rows    4
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
+ I *$0Launch.(1x3+0+0, Icon $1, Action (Mouse 1) `Exec $2`)
               ^^^^^^^
+ I *$0Launch.Pixmap none
+ I *$0Launch.(1x1+0+3, Font 9x15bold, Fore White, Back DarkBlue, Title $0, Action (Mouse 1) `Exec $2`)
               ^^^^^^^
+ I Style $0Launch. HandleWidth 0, NoTitle
+ I Module FvwmButtons $3 $0Launch.
# Examples:
Launcher rxvt xterm.xpm "rxvt" "-g +0+0"
Launcher xv   xv.xpm    "xv"   "-g +0+72"

2) Use a colour set instead of Back/Fore to get rid of this
   ugly border around the icon title, 

3) I'd not use a bold font for the icon titles.

4) We need an 'icon box' for windows (a 'window box' :-) ).
   This way these icons could easily be lined up without
   specifying a geometry.

Bye

Dominik ^_^

