Dan Espen wrote:
 
> As long as Colorsets  sit in an optional module  they don't  seem like
> core  functionality.  Anyone else think Colorsets  should be moved out
> of module land before 2.4?

Personally I'm quite happy with a module.  I can't see any
advantage in having this in the main module other than speed -
and speed is currently no critical factor in FvwmTheme.

Olivier Chapuis wrote:

> Mikhael Goikhman wrote:
> > 
> > Probably not a very easy task to do now. Not that I am against.
> 
> I think it is a good idea to move FvwmTheme into fvwm since
> the "good way" to use colors in fvwm is to use FvwmTheme.
> If there is a volunteer for doing that I think he may try
> to convince Mikhael to remove his negative vote.

See above.

> But most important from my point of view is that we may try
> to do so that FvwmTheme is fully functional for fvwm before 2.4:
> currently only fg, bg, hi and sh is used in Title and Border.
> If nobody plan to do this I'm ready if there is two votes for
> that and no vote against.

FvwmTheme *is* fully functional.  Fvwm can't handle the
pixmaps provided by FvwmTheme everywhere.  We can't simply put
a pixmap from FvwmTheme on window borders/titles because

 1) Gradients would have to be drawn manually each time the
    title is updated.  This is too slow with the way that
    FvwmTheme (or a reimplementation in the main module) works.
    It will require a major redesign/enhancement of FvwmTheme
    to achieve an acceptable speed.
 2) ...Style can't use stacked pixmaps with FvwmTheme.

I'm absolutely against starting this now.  We really need to
focus on fixing the many bugs in the current cvs.  I promise to
provide an updated to-do list for 2.4 (containing all the bugs
that have queued up in my mail) until the end of the week.

Bye

Dominik ^_^

