Ugh, I was going to suggest a:

DestroyModuleConfig FvwmIconMan*transient*dontshow*

until I remembered that FvwmIconMan uses '*' to separate configuration
subparts, which is inconvenient if you're trying to
DestroyModuleConfig. I think this is bad.  FvwmIconMan and
DestroyModuleConfig shouldn't find the same character interesting in
different ways.

In the meantime, you might be able to escape the non-terminating
asterisks, but I just don't know what fvwm does inside of
DestroyModuleConfig.
