I just came to the realization of something.

fvwm-config -c is wherever the ./configure --sysconfdir=/blah

Fvwm's default Script's are also placed in that same directory along with
the system.fvwm2rc. I don't think this should be done. The etcdir is used
for configuration, not scripts.

This came to me, while discussing with migo about fvwm-themes, how it
will use fvwm-config -c + /fvwm
Themes also do not belong in the etcdir,. They belong more in the
share/fvwm. Just like scripts and such.  

Almost every distribution uses /etc/X11/fvwm or /etc/X11/fvwm2 for it's
sysconfdir. And Scripts and themes should _never_ be put in a
configuration directory tree. As standard, themes and such would normally
be in the PREFIX/share/software-name, such would be /usr/share/fvwm/ or
/usr/local/share/fvwm (by default compiling method).

I'd like to see what you guys say to this. This is kind of a major issue
in theme-engine creation, and even pure standards.

