I am not quoting the original message, because it contains unrelevant (and
sometimes not exact) info. Here is the rewording of the raised problem.

We have in fvwm:
  FVWM_MODULEDIR='${libexecdir}/${PACKAGE}/${VERSION}'
  FVWM_CONFIGDIR='${sysconfdir}/${PACKAGE}'

In FVWM_CONFIGDIR currently we install configs (Config*), scripts
(Script*), and forms (Form*), I think none of them belong to $sysconfdir,
i.e. there is nothing that fvwm may want to install to /etc (if distros
use /etc for ${sysconfdir}).

So the fix is to change the second line to something like:
  FVWM_CONFIGDIR='${datadir}/${PACKAGE}'

where ${datadir} is usually ${prefix}/share or similar.
I will care about this if you all agree with it.

Regards,
Mikhael.
