Hello,
For me the choice between etc/ and share/ is not important.
The important point is the logic that use fvwm to read
configuration files: it first look the FVWM_USERHOME or
to HOME and then if the config file is not found it
look in the fvwm config dir (no exported variable here).
(there is also the complete path but here we found the
config file or we fail!).
There is a gap in my opinion in this procedure. Where
we install complex config system? (as fvwm-themes or
others). To take advantage of the above reading strategy
one want to install it in the fvwm config dir and this
is not "clean" and may cause some problems (we've got
some with fvwm-themes). So, the other alternative is to
install everything in the fvwm user home (and some none root
user must do such a things). Again, this is bad! I can
give some (technical) argument if you want.
The good place for complex config system is a 3rd directory
say share/name-of-the-theme-engine/* (share or pouf this
not really important but share seems good). Then, the "reading"
strategy will insert this new dir between the two others.
For that we can just allows FVWM_USERHOME to be "multidir"
as the Image Path so FVWM_USERHOME can be
        my_personal_stuff:dir_of_the_complex_engine
And every thing will be perfect in a marvelous world.
Olivier
