I learned opinions voiced here in the last several months (plus archives).
I have a working patch, that solves most of the problems discussed.
This patch can be posted on request, it is long, because of renamings.
It does not break anything, at least I don't see what it can break.
I need 2 votes to apply this patch and no votes against.

What this patch does:

All fvwm data, which was in sysconfdir subdir, is now in datadir subdir.
fvwm still tries $sysconfdir/system.fvwm2rc if finds nothing else.

FVWM_USERHOME is renamed to FVWM_USERDIR for consistency, the old variable
name is still supported (but could be removed before 2.4, I suppose).

FVWM_USERDIR now defaults to $HOME/.fvwm not $HOME. FVWM_USERDIR directory
is now created if needed. FVWM_USERDIR variable is now exported for all
subprocesses, not only for modules (just like FVWM_MODULEDIR).

fvwm still searches for $HOME/.fvwm2rc for compatibility; but Read doesn't
specially supports $HOME (I don't think this is needed, but can be added).

This patch does not contradict with the Olivier's suggestion (corrected
by me) to add additional SearchPath to extend FVWM_USERDIR & FVWM_DATADIR.

Regards,
Mikhael.
