Okay. I looked harder. It looks like for the problem of root
keybindings, I'd randomly picked the unfortunate binding

Key Escape A C Module FvwmIdent

This doesn't ever appear to work, since the Escape gets passed to
FvwmIdent, cancelling the selection process. Or that's my guess. Other
root key bindings seem to work. For my other problem (invoking from a
menu), it appears to be caused only when you use a key selection in
the menu. Clicking the menu seems to be fine. The following minimalist
config should do it:

AddToMenu Window Ident Module FvwmIdent
Key F1 A N Menu Window

Regardless of focus policy, etc., if you popup the menu from the root
context and attempt to select this item using menu-based key
navigation (space or enter to select), FvwmIdent doesn't wait for you
to select a window. It does work if I assign a hotkey like "&Ident"
and select using "I".

So... after experimenting with FvwmIdent in "crosshair window select
mode" is that escape, space and return all end the selection process.
Escape cancels and space/return mimic Button 1 (select whatever's
under the cursor). Now, this means that in the configs I describe
above (maybe all?), Key Events that selected FvwmIdent to run are
"bleeding" into FvwmIdent's event queue... Can anything be done about
this? I'm chiefly concerned about the case of selecting FvwmIdent out
of a popped-up menu from the root context, using standard fvwm
key-based menu navigation.
