I see what you mean. Still, I think it's a bad model that menus appear
to invoke their bound actions on KeyPress yet
fvwmlib_get_target_window() watches KeyReleases. It allows
menu-bindings that cause fvwmlib_get_target_window() to be invoked to
have their KeyRelease events be picked up by the module that was
invoked. I can't imagine this is desirable. It appears that
FvwmDragWell and FvwmScroll also use this function, but no others. Can
we patch this?
