Sorry, try as I might - I can't find a situation where it doesn't work.
There are two places in virtual.c where the MapDesk function is called.
In both places, a BroadcastRestack is sent for all windows.  So, unless
the stacking chain is out of order it can't happen.  Did you really
*lower* the sticky window?  Or did you *raise* other windows above it?
In the latter case, if you switch to a different page and/or desk, the
window may be on top of the windows in the current viewport.  It's only
a bug if the pager doesn't reflect the actual stacking order properly.

